result.execSummary:
Jolene Jeanetta was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jolene Jeanetta was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jolene M Jeanetta in court with attorney Shelly Tomtschik- who has not been retained.  Defendant Jolene M Jeanetta in custody.  Daniel Joseph Tolan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  KJB- Clerk. 1:14pm State gives Def a copy of CC and waiver of extradition. Def has not contacted PDs office- must contact PDs office to see if qualify. State of MN- Pine County reqs extradition. Def does not voluntarily wish to waive extradition. Jail will let Def call PDs office. CT has advised of rights. Def wishes to waive extradition. Incorrect Date of birth: 12/2/1979. DAs office will prepare new ones immediately. 1:22pm break.  CT enters NG plea to Misd. CT preserves all rights of substitution,  pre plea motions and WTL. Def signs corrected extradition forms.  CT signs forms. Def acknow that signed of own free will- FV.  1:33PM ADJ.  Status conference scheduled for September 12, 2014 at 09:45 am.
